The Sports Writers Association of Nigeria (SWAN), Oyo State chapter, has commiserated with General Manager, Shooting Stars Sports Club (3SC), Mr Rasheed Balogun over the death of his wife, Alhaja Sadiat Sodiya Balogun. In a condolence message released on Monday by the Chairman Oyo SWAN, Mr Niyi Alebiosu and the Secretary Mr Adewale Tijani, the Association of sportswriters in the state described the death of 3SC General Manager’s wife as “saddening and unfortunate.” ALSO READ: LAUTECH workers urge Makinde, Oyetola to resolve institution’s crisis LAUTECH workers urge Makinde, Oyetola to resolve… Nationwide Strike: FG, Labour in ‘make or mar’… We have zero-tolerance for thu­ggery ― Edo govt Police uncover 360 chained children at religious centre in… Oyo SWAN described the death of Alhaja Sadiat Sodiya Balogun as shocking and touching to the entire 3SC family and football fraternity in the country. The Association prayed for the repose of the soul of the deceased and also prayed that God grant the bereaved sports administrator the fortitude to bear the great loss. Alhaja Sadiat Anike Sodiya Balogun died on Sunday morning and has been buried in accordance with Islamic rites. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
